<item>
            <title>[FLINK-25446] Avoid sanity check on read bytes on DataInputStream#read(byte[])</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-25446</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Current changelog related code would check the number of read bytes whether equal to target bytes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
checkState(size == input.read(bytes));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this is not correct as the java doc said: &lt;tt&gt;&quot;An attempt is made to read as many as len bytes, but a smaller number may be read, possibly zero.&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
